Paolo Scaroni: &quot;Elliott's strategy is to bring Milan back to its rightful position despite the constraints of Financial Fair Play.&quot;<br />
<br />
Leonardo: &quot;I have also met other people, not just Juventus. We are still linked to FFP, so it won't be a crazy transfer market, but a wise, intelligent and moderate transfer market.&quot;

Leonardo: &quot;Bonucci? I think it's normal that a player asks about the situation he currently is in, the project, the goals and the balance of the market. We will evaluate what we will do with Bonucci.&quot;<br />
<br />
Leonardo: &quot;Huge wages is  going to affect us, so it will be more difficult to get these big names.&quot;
